            <h3>Attribute Recognition</h3>
            <p> This is an on going project where I am attempting to use images (and video) and related sentences to quickly predict attributes present in regions of an image. So basically not just object recognition but also adjective predictions like round, shiny, or even large. I am currently using OpenNI with a Primesense (Kinect like RGBD) camera, as well as convolutional neural networks implemented on the GPU to attempt this. So far I have a simple version that uses SVMs which shows an ability to predict some colors, positions, and general shapes (round), and the current network version which is only trained to recognize objects until I can rewrite a portion of it to work with multilabel prediction, ie it can predict that and object is "red, yellow or blue," but not "red, yellow and blue."</p>
