            <h3>DTW on Google N-Grams</h3>
            <p> This was a really fun project whihc I did not continue since it had little to do with my work, but I continue to hold out hope that I can return to it. The idea was to find interesting patterns in Google N-Grams. SO I downloaded a copy, and began working wiht it in Scala, which I was trying to learn at the time. I used Dynamic Time Warping given a word, to find words that peaked in usage at the same time. So for example if you ask <a href="https://books.google.com/ngrams/graph?content=end%2Cwar%2Cgun&year_start=1900&year_end=1980&corpus=15&smoothing=3&share=&direct_url=t1%3B%2Cend%3B%2Cc0%3B.t1%3B%2Cwar%3B%2Cc0%3B.t1%3B%2Cgun%3B%2Cc0">Google N-Grams</a> to display "war","gun","end" at the same time, they all spike in usage during wars. I had this working, but only on a very narrow subset: I had no experience with databases, and no idea how to quickly access the data, so as a proof of concept I had taken a 100 words, some of which were obviously related and others which were not and tried a few searches on them. I had further plans, but have not reurned to it.</p>
